> Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our
> Fragrant Teriyaki Pork Rice Bowl in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy
> meal.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams}, ~{12-13%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the
mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.
IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no
pink in the middle.
Meanwhile, cut the @Lime{1}(quartered) into quarters and open the remaining
sachets.

Add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams}, @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and
@Ginger, Garlic & Lemongrass Puree{15%grams} to the mince. Stir-fry, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @Teriyaki Sauce{100%grams}, @Soy Sauce{15%milliliters},
@Water{50%milliliters} for the sauce and a squeeze of lime juice. Simmer,
~{2-3%minutes}.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} or lime juice if needed.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the pork.

Drizzle over the @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and sprinkle with the
@Black Sesame Seeds{5%grams}.

Serve the remaining lime wedges alongside.

Enjoy!